  "target_response": {
    "text": "You didn't screw up your cut — that kilo is almost certainly water, not fat. Creatine pulls water into muscle cells, and a gain of roughly 1 kg in the first couple of weeks is the textbook response. It stays as long as you keep taking it, and because it sits inside the muscle it tends to make you look fuller rather than softer. Your actual cut is judged by the trend underneath: at 78.4 kg now with a 76 kg target, keep the deficit as planned and expect the scale to resume its slow drift within a week or two, just starting from a slightly higher waterline. If the weekly average is still flat after three or four weeks, adjust intake then — because of the food, not the creatine. No reason to stop a supplement that's doing its normal, harmless thing.",
